React Router Documentation

1.What is react-router?
React Router is a standard library for routing in React applications. It enables navigation among different components, changing the browser URL, and keeping the UI in sync with the URL.

2. Key Concepts
a. Router
A router component wraps your entire application and enables routing features.

b. Routes
A container for all route definitions.

c. Route
Defines a path and the component to render.

d. Link / NavLink
Used for navigation between pages without full reload.

e. useNavigate
A hook for programmatic navigation.

f. useParams
A hook to extract URL parameters.

3. Installation
npm install react-router-dom

4. Basic Setup


import { BrowserRouter, Routes, Route } from 'react-router-dom';
import Home from './Home';
import About from './About';

function App() {
  return (
    <BrowserRouter>
      <Routes>
        <Route path="/" element={<Home />} />
        <Route path="/about" element={<About />} />
      </Routes>
    </BrowserRouter>
  );
}
export default App;

5. Navigation
Using Link

import { Link } from 'react-router-dom';
<Link to="/about">Go to About</Link>


Using NavLink (with active styling)
<NavLink to="/about" className={({ isActive }) => isActive ? 'active' : ''}>
  About
</NavLink>

6. URL Parameters
<Route path="/user/:id" element={<User />} />

Extracting params:
import { useParams } from 'react-router-dom';

function User() {
  const { id } = useParams();
  return <h1>User ID: {id}</h1>;
}

7. Programmatic Navigation
import { useNavigate } from 'react-router-dom';
const navigate = useNavigate();
navigate('/dashboard');

8. Nested Routes
<Route path="dashboard" element={<Dashboard />}>
  <Route path="stats" element={<Stats />} />
</Route>

Render child route with `Outlet`:
import { Outlet } from 'react-router-dom';

function Dashboard() {
  return (
    <div>
      <h2>Dashboard</h2>
      <Outlet />
    </div>
  );
}

9. Protected Routes
function Protected({ children }) {
  const isAuth = localStorage.getItem('token');
  return isAuth ? children : <Navigate to="/login" />;
}

<Route path="/profile" element={<Protected><Profile /></Protected>} />

10. Error or Not Found Page
<Route path="*" element={<NotFound />} />
